<div class='panel'><p>A <em>generalist</em> Mastodon instance hosted in <em>France</em>.</p>

<hr />

<p>
Our guidelines are currently being written ; but basically:
</p>

<ul>
<li>don't be a dick,</li>
<li>no advertising, harassment, spam,</li>
<li>no abuse on the API by local users (bots, ...),</li>
<li>Any thing illegal under the French law will be removed and reported to the competent authorities.</li>
</ul>

<p>
Informations and status about the instance is posted to <a href="/@admin">@admin</a>.

Currently the only human administrating this instance is <a href="/@href">@href</a>. Other administrators may be added in the future, as I (href) prefer focusing on managing the servers and the underlying infrastructure than people.
<br/>
<br/>
Don't hesitate to ping either @href or @admin to talk about the instance, create an issue at <a href="https://github.com/hrefhref/mastodon/issues">hrefhref/mastodon</a> on GitHub, or privately at <code>admin (at) soc.ialis.me</code>.
</p>

<p>The instance itself is hosted on servers at <a href="https://online.net">Online.net</a> and <a href="http://scaleway.com">Scaleway.com</a>, in Paris, France. The database and files are frequently replicated on a couple of servers, and externally backuped.
<br/><br/>
The servers are run by an organization <i>(with no legal grounds; entierly privately owned)</i>  called <a href="https://random.sh">random.sh</a> / <a href="https://randomlabs.co">random labs</a>; which hosts other services such as irc.random.sh, a ChatSpike.net IRC Server, <a href="http://etherpad.fr">Etherpad.fr</a>, and much more. I also intend to one day make it my own company for some products, but I'll then separate the business with theses community services (the business will just be a sponsor, and without any advertisement, tracking, or anything else evil).

</p>

